FBIS4-61387 "drsov088_g_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-088 Daily Report 5 May 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus Country Needs $8 Million To Scrap Military Technology Country Needs $8 Million To Scrap Military Technology MK0505102094 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 5 May 94 p 1 MK0505102094 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA Russian BFN [Report by Valeriy Kovalev report under the "News" rubric: "No Getting Rid of Vast `Collection' of Arms Without Help"] [Text] Minsk -- The National Agency for Control and Inspections (NACI) has officially denied reports alleging that Belorussia [Belarus] has suspended the elimination of military technology under the Treaty on Conventional Arms Reduction in Europe. It is thought in the NACI that Belorussia would require at least $8 million to fully honor the obligations under the treaty. Belorussia's repeated appeals to Western states in this regard, however, have elicited no response.
